    h3 Find a space to grow your idea or event!

    p Community groups can search for and connect with empty offices, storefronts or even vacant lots and fill them with their events and activities. Spaces range from free to medium in cost and vary in neighborhood, size and functionality. We hope you find a space to grow your idea or event!


    h2.home About CivicSpaces

    div.row
      div.col-md-8
        p CivicSpaces is a site to help active citizens, artists and nonprofits find unused spaces to host their events and display their creative work. We serve as a conduit, connecting owners of empty spaces with people who want to fill them for a short-term project, event or activity. 

        p Building owners who have vacant storefronts, office space or even empty lots can offer their space through CivicSpaces to attract artists and nonprofits to fill them with life for a short period of time. There are many studies showing that active spaces are more attractive and easier to rent than empty ones. Having active offices and storefronts can lead to more foot traffic, increasing an areas visibility and reducing crime. 

        p We want to keep our city vibrant, one empty space at a time. 

