    h2.home Spaces

    div.row
      div.col-md-8
        p Do you have an unused office, retail storefront or loft? How about a vacant lot? CivicSpaces can help you partner with community activists who can bring your space to life. Whether its a nonprofit needing temporary office space or an arts group looking for a pop-up gallery store front, CivicSpaces aims to fill your empty square feet with life. Not only could you receive tax benefits* but filling unused space with activity makes it instantly more desirable, resulting in the higher likelihood in a profitable lease or sale. 

        p *please consult your tax professional 

        h3 Who Qualifies? 
        p We accept any space that is in sound condition, meeting local structural and health standards, that is willing to host civic minded groups or individuals in the space for a limited time with little to no financial cost to the participating group or individual. We welcome empty storefronts, office buildings, lofts and vacant lots. Our listing page allows you to set the rules for potential users- what they can do in your space, what times they can be there and how long you are willing to host them. Additionally you may require interim leasees to provide a deposit or pay for utility costs, depending on your needs. 

        h3 What events and activities do you promote? 
        p CivicSpaces encourages groups and active citizens to fill our city’s vacant spaces with creative events and displays. The types of events and displays you or your company is comfortable with is up to you and the suitability of your space and business brand. We promote and attract the following types of activities:

        ul.list-group
          li.list-group-item gallery-style installations 
          li.list-group-item sculptures
          li.list-group-item human interest displays (like informative displays around local or regional issues, nonprofit sponsored art or photography displays, graphics or charts informing citizens)
          li.list-group-item non-permanent gardens/farms 
          li.list-group-item fundraising events 
          li.list-group-item informative events 
          li.list-group-item limited-time office or meeting space
          li.list-group-item community gatherings
          li.list-group-item coordinated efforts of any of the above (events/groups looking to fill multiple spaces during a coordinated time- see our Sponsored Event section for details). 

        h3 What You Should Know
        p Currently CivicSpaces only provides you information about what spaces are willing to participate in a civic activity. We do not book spaces, arrange contracts or take on any responsibility for the space-to-citizen transaction. Please consult a legal professional should you have any concerns. By posting on our site you agree to our terms and conditions and acknowledge that your contact information will be available on the site until you remove it. We have provided a list of resources and materials to help you navigate hosting an event or activity in a vacant space. These materials are only meant to be helpful resources and are not a guarantee of a successful or incident free space-to-citizen interaction.